WEBVTT

00:02.917 --> 00:06.792
SAM: <i>There comes a time in everyone's</i>
<i>life when they have to leave the nest.</i>

00:06.792 --> 00:08.500
<i>Me, I've had two times.</i>

00:08.500 --> 00:11.667
<i>Because after a year of recovering</i>
<i>from amnesia at my parents' house,</i>

00:11.667 --> 00:14.291
<i>I was ready to either</i>
<i>spread my wings and fly</i>

00:15.792 --> 00:19.041
<i>or fall to the ground</i>
<i>and get swallowed by a snake.</i>

00:19.041 --> 00:20.500
Okay, Mom. Mom.

00:20.500 --> 00:21.959
Dad? Dad, can you--?

00:23.917 --> 00:25.583
Regina.

00:25.583 --> 00:27.458
Release.

00:28.458 --> 00:30.208
Okay.

00:33.583 --> 00:36.208
Frank, make sure she uses condoms.

00:39.125 --> 00:40.709
Okay.

00:43.625 --> 00:46.875
Oh, my God, Frank.
I'm home. I have my own place.

00:46.875 --> 00:49.291
Can you believe it?
I can do whatever I want.

00:49.291 --> 00:52.083
I can sing, I can run around naked.

00:52.083 --> 00:55.750
You can learn to tip,
as long as you're making a list.

00:55.750 --> 00:57.917
[GABRIELLA CILMI'S
"SAVE THE LIES" PLAYING]

00:57.917 --> 00:59.917
[SINGING]

01:17.959 --> 01:19.959
[HUMMING]

01:21.250 --> 01:24.000
- I love this song. Aah!
- Aah!

01:26.208 --> 01:27.792
Todd.

01:27.792 --> 01:30.917
I thought when we talked on the phone
you said you were moving out.

01:30.917 --> 01:33.792
I was. I am. I'm on my way
to look at a few places right now.

01:33.792 --> 01:35.792
Really?
Are you sure you're not just stalling

01:35.792 --> 01:37.834
because you think
I'm gonna change my mind?

01:37.834 --> 01:40.333
Because you know what,
if that's the case, I just--

01:40.333 --> 01:44.000
I feel it's gonna be really weird
for both of us, you know?

01:45.000 --> 01:46.834
Huh? Oh.

01:46.834 --> 01:47.959
Apartments.

01:48.917 --> 01:51.583
Bay windows. That sounds nice.

01:51.583 --> 01:52.959
Yeah.

01:53.625 --> 01:55.959
Hello?

01:55.959 --> 01:57.959
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

01:59.333 --> 02:01.750
Mom? Dad?

02:01.750 --> 02:03.917
Hello.

02:05.542 --> 02:08.417
- Oh.
- Sweetheart, you're home.

02:08.417 --> 02:12.250
- Hey, you look kind of thin.
- She's been gone six hours.

02:12.250 --> 02:14.542
I have to do laundry.
Plus, I need to take your spatula

02:14.542 --> 02:17.583
because Todd used mine
to clean hair out of the drain.

02:17.583 --> 02:20.208
- What are you guys doing?
- We're practicing for the contest

02:20.208 --> 02:21.875
at the Walnut Valley Club next week.

02:23.208 --> 02:25.333
[SAMANTHA LAUGHING]

02:25.333 --> 02:27.041
How old are you guys there?

02:27.041 --> 02:29.125
You look so dorky.

02:29.125 --> 02:30.542
- That was last year.
- Oh.

02:30.542 --> 02:32.125
We're using this as a training film.

02:32.125 --> 02:34.291
Look, watch, Howard.

02:34.625 --> 02:37.125
There, right there. See?
Our footwork is really sloppy.

02:37.125 --> 02:38.375
HOWARD:
I think we look pretty good.

02:38.375 --> 02:40.291
Pretty good's not enough
to beat Paula Drake.

02:40.291 --> 02:42.041
Oh, I see what this is about.

02:42.041 --> 02:44.458
Your little rivalry with Paula Drake.

02:44.458 --> 02:46.375
Yes, it is. Her and her smug little grin.

02:46.375 --> 02:48.125
She beats me at everything.

02:48.125 --> 02:51.250
This and best tulips,
and best chili cook-off.

02:51.250 --> 02:53.875
Oh, and that daughter of hers,
she's a doctor,

02:53.875 --> 02:56.458
she's married, she has two children.

02:56.458 --> 02:59.125
You know, and you're single
and you're unemployed,

02:59.125 --> 03:02.458
and after your coma,
you had to re-learn how to peel an orange.

03:02.458 --> 03:04.375
Hey, I got that in one day.

03:04.834 --> 03:08.291
We've gotta practice that grapevine
or we're never gonna get first place.

03:08.291 --> 03:11.083
Third place is a screwdriver set.
That's something we could use.

03:11.083 --> 03:12.583
Hey. Hey, what's this?

03:17.375 --> 03:19.250
It's one of your college recitals.

03:19.250 --> 03:21.959
I was in a recital and you taped over it?

03:21.959 --> 03:25.208
How was I supposed to know
you wanted to see that again?

03:25.208 --> 03:28.000
What am I supposed to think
every time I wanna tape an <i>Oprah</i>, that,

03:28.000 --> 03:30.500
"Oh, Sam might get amnesia.

03:30.500 --> 03:33.000
She might wanna see
that first birthday party"?

03:35.208 --> 03:36.291
I used to dance.

03:37.291 --> 03:39.750
You know, I don't wanna sound conceited
or anything,

03:40.041 --> 03:41.792
but I'm pretty badass.

03:41.792 --> 03:44.583
HOWARD: Hey, you were incredible.
REGINA: Yeah, you take that from me.

03:44.583 --> 03:47.250
- Feel that thigh.
- Yeah, hard as a rock. Feel it.

03:47.250 --> 03:49.792
Later. Why didn't you tell me?

03:49.792 --> 03:52.166
I mean, you point out
every lousy thing about my life,

03:52.166 --> 03:55.417
but the one talent that I do have,
nobody mentions it?

03:55.417 --> 03:57.625
We didn't want you to get a big head.

03:57.959 --> 04:00.875
I wanna see it again. I wanna see it again.
Come on. Come on.

04:07.583 --> 04:09.959
Shouldn't you be hunting
for apartments?

04:09.959 --> 04:12.208
I set a few traps.
I'll check them tomorrow.

04:13.000 --> 04:16.041
I know your game. You have no intention
of looking for an apartment.

04:16.041 --> 04:18.291
You're just gonna keep
mooching off Sam.

04:18.291 --> 04:20.125
I was looking, okay?

04:20.125 --> 04:22.375
I thought I had money
coming from this wedding I shot,

04:22.375 --> 04:24.959
but the bride, you know,
she didn't like the proofs.

04:24.959 --> 04:28.041
She's just not going to pay? And you're
gonna let her get away with that?

04:28.041 --> 04:30.333
I left messages, e-mail.
I don't know what else to do.

04:30.333 --> 04:32.250
I'm an attorney.
Come to my office tomorrow

04:32.250 --> 04:34.291
and I'll show you what else you can do.

04:34.291 --> 04:37.500
I just told you.
I don't have money for a lawyer.

04:37.500 --> 04:38.625
Are you slow?

04:38.625 --> 04:42.125
Look, I get to bring a bride to tears
and kick you out of Sam's apartment?

04:42.125 --> 04:43.333
I should be paying you.

04:47.333 --> 04:49.792
You know what, we should
switch things out before we go.

04:49.792 --> 04:53.375
That paper-towel holder
goes home with me,

04:53.375 --> 04:56.625
the spatula goes back
to the city with you.

04:56.625 --> 04:57.959
Look at you.

04:57.959 --> 04:59.792
You're all grown up.

04:59.792 --> 05:01.291
You got your own spatula.

05:02.125 --> 05:03.583
I did a good job.

05:03.583 --> 05:06.041
- Oh, crap!
- What, what, what?

05:06.041 --> 05:07.375
Paula Drake.

05:07.375 --> 05:09.500
I should never leave the house
without a bra.

05:09.500 --> 05:12.083
I don't think we need Paula Drake
to make that a rule, Mom.

05:12.083 --> 05:14.458
- What are you doing?
- Putting on lipstick.

05:14.458 --> 05:16.125
She's my nemesis.

05:16.125 --> 05:17.625
She's your nemesis?

05:17.625 --> 05:19.500
What is she?
Does she have an underground lair?

05:20.208 --> 05:21.834
Regina.

05:21.834 --> 05:24.709
- Hi.
- I thought that was you.

05:24.709 --> 05:27.500
What are you doing here?
Buying a bra, I hope.

05:27.500 --> 05:29.041
Hi, Paula.

05:29.041 --> 05:30.250
Samantha.

05:30.250 --> 05:31.917
Hello.

05:31.917 --> 05:34.792
How is your head injury doing today?

05:34.792 --> 05:39.208
I'm not brain-damaged.
I have my own spatula.

05:40.041 --> 05:43.834
Oh, Regina, did I see that you signed up
for the dance at the club again?

05:44.583 --> 05:46.000
Yes, you did. Yes, you did.

05:46.000 --> 05:47.792
In fact, I think Howard and I

05:47.792 --> 05:50.333
are gonna give you and Charlie
a run for your money this year.

05:50.333 --> 05:51.959
Of course you will.

05:51.959 --> 05:54.792
Like I said at the
Chandlers' anniversary party--

05:54.792 --> 05:57.458
Oh, faux pas. Were you not invited?

05:57.959 --> 05:59.500
Anyway, I told everyone

05:59.500 --> 06:01.667
that no matter how many times
the Newlys lose,

06:01.667 --> 06:03.125
they just keep on going.

06:03.125 --> 06:05.458
They may be failures,
but they are not quitters.

06:05.458 --> 06:07.875
Hey, they're not failures either.

06:07.875 --> 06:09.000
Of course they're not.

06:09.417 --> 06:12.000
Will you have a special seat
to watch your parents lose?

06:12.583 --> 06:14.709
She won't be there.
She's moved back to the city.

06:14.709 --> 06:17.333
No, I'll be there.
Because we're going to kick your butts.

06:17.333 --> 06:20.166
- We?
- Yep, that's right. I am your new partner.

06:20.166 --> 06:22.083
And I am excellent.

06:22.083 --> 06:24.291
Two women can't dance together
at the club.

06:24.291 --> 06:26.250
Oh, yes, they can,

06:26.250 --> 06:29.417
thanks to those two nice gay lawyers
who just moved down the block.

06:29.417 --> 06:31.000
It's a whole new world.

06:31.000 --> 06:33.959
Yeah, well, we made them cry,
and we'll make you cry too.

06:33.959 --> 06:37.125
You wanna see some crying?
We're gonna bring you to your knees.

06:37.125 --> 06:40.500
And not in some cool dance-move way.
Ahh...

06:40.500 --> 06:42.250
- What just happened?
- I don't know.

06:42.250 --> 06:44.750
But I got that same high I got
when I peeled that orange.

06:44.750 --> 06:45.792
[LAUGHING]

06:55.375 --> 06:57.166
I don't know how it came out of me.

06:57.166 --> 07:00.625
It's just that this Paula Drake woman
was attacking my family

07:00.625 --> 07:02.959
and all of a sudden
I just became, like, a mother cat.

07:02.959 --> 07:04.667
And my mom was my kitten

07:04.667 --> 07:07.166
and she was being swallowed
by a python or something.

07:07.166 --> 07:09.625
- Oh, pythons gotta eat.
- What?

07:09.625 --> 07:12.000
Not a kitten person.
Surprising, I know, but--

07:12.500 --> 07:15.875
Excuse me, dance competition?
Why didn't you tell me about this?

07:15.875 --> 07:19.083
- Oh, because I usually just--
- We're in. I have magic legs.

07:19.083 --> 07:22.166
- Ha.
- No, we're not-- We're not dancing.

07:22.166 --> 07:24.792
What do you mean we're not--?
We can win.

07:24.792 --> 07:26.375
- You are going down, Newly.
- No.

07:26.375 --> 07:28.208
We can dance any other night
of the year.

07:28.208 --> 07:32.000
But the Walnut Valley Dance Competition
is the one night I get to be on tech crew.

07:32.917 --> 07:37.417
If it makes you feel any better, though,
my mom and I are kind of a lock to win.

07:37.417 --> 07:40.667
- So two women dancing.
- Mm-hm.

07:42.375 --> 07:44.792
- You're thinking where the boobs go?
- Anyone would.

07:44.792 --> 07:47.709
So how's your dad, you know,
with you stepping in?

07:47.709 --> 07:50.000
I don't know, she's telling him right now.

07:50.000 --> 07:53.333
God, I feel so bad, though, because
he looks forward to this every year.

07:53.333 --> 07:56.625
Thank you, gay-lawyer couple!

07:56.625 --> 08:00.291
Have fun with Sam.
I'm off to the boat show.

08:00.291 --> 08:01.500
[LAUGHING]

08:01.500 --> 08:03.166
Whoo!

08:04.875 --> 08:08.208
We're thinking about doing a cha-cha,
but we haven't figured it out yet.

08:08.208 --> 08:10.417
We're gonna get
these little matching gold dresses.

08:10.417 --> 08:13.917
Oh, God, it's going to feel so good
to take this Paula Drake down.

08:13.917 --> 08:16.166
Paula Drake, little matching dresses.

08:16.166 --> 08:19.250
I'm making sure I have all the details
for when I repeat the story at work.

08:19.250 --> 08:21.250
You are so not interested in this.

08:21.250 --> 08:24.083
No, I am not interested in this,
and why are you?

08:24.500 --> 08:27.834
I mean, you are finally out of the sticks,
Todd is almost out of the apartment.

08:27.834 --> 08:30.083
You're healing. Don't open the wound.

08:30.083 --> 08:31.834
This means so much to my mother.

08:32.667 --> 08:35.417
Okay, maybe I'm not drinking enough,
because this is unclear.

08:35.417 --> 08:38.792
You don't like your mother,
you don't show up at Thanksgivings.

08:38.792 --> 08:41.583
You send your assistant
to birthday parties,

08:41.583 --> 08:43.709
you don't do Christmas.

08:43.709 --> 08:45.333
Oh, sweet baby Jesus.

08:47.709 --> 08:50.458
Where are these judges?
It's freezing out here.

08:50.458 --> 08:53.458
Well, maybe if a certain shepherd
didn't dress like a $2 whore.

08:53.458 --> 08:55.917
- I have a date in half an hour.
- Oh, no, you don't.

08:55.917 --> 08:58.834
It is Christmas Eve, young lady.
You get back here right now.

08:58.834 --> 09:01.917
- You are a member of this family.
- Really? Where do I sign to get out?

09:01.917 --> 09:04.125
Do not make me
put down this baby Jesus!

09:04.125 --> 09:05.458
[HOWARD SINGING "SILENT NIGHT"]

09:05.458 --> 09:09.750
Okay, God, I can't wait to put you
in a home. Really. Oh, God.

09:10.083 --> 09:11.250
[GASPS]

09:11.250 --> 09:13.667
There, I just won you a free ham.

09:16.583 --> 09:19.750
I like it. I think it's edgy.

09:20.583 --> 09:23.917
Okay, well, now I am
making it up to her,

09:23.917 --> 09:25.709
especially if we win.

09:25.709 --> 09:27.959
Because do you know
how good of a dancer I am?

09:27.959 --> 09:31.208
Uh, yes, I do.
We used to go dancing all the time.

09:31.208 --> 09:35.417
Oh, you used to shake it,
and you used to have everyone watching,

09:35.417 --> 09:38.166
and then I would swoop in
and I would just spank your ass.

09:38.166 --> 09:39.500
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING]

09:40.083 --> 09:41.333
I love this song.

09:42.208 --> 09:43.583
ANDREA:
Yes.

09:59.917 --> 10:01.125
[LAUGHS]

10:01.125 --> 10:03.959
Well, don't just stand there, spank me!

10:13.792 --> 10:16.000
Okay, you can do this.

10:16.000 --> 10:17.417
You know how to dance.

10:17.417 --> 10:19.417
[MUSIC PLAYING ON TV]

10:46.625 --> 10:48.083
[MUSIC STOPS]

10:48.083 --> 10:49.250
[SIGHS]

10:49.250 --> 10:50.875
Bitch.

10:53.959 --> 10:56.250
Samantha,

10:56.458 --> 10:58.834
get up off the floor.

10:58.834 --> 11:01.917
When your father pulls in, he doesn't stop
until he hits that tennis ball.

11:03.041 --> 11:07.792
I talked to my doctor today
and I have lost my ability to dance.

11:07.792 --> 11:11.458
Oh, please. I swear,
that man just says things to upset me.

11:12.000 --> 11:16.709
Ow. No, Mom, it's the amnesia.
He says it happens all the time.

11:16.709 --> 11:20.792
He's seen people lose their ability
to play the piano or to speak French.

11:20.792 --> 11:22.458
Last night I tried to dance at a club,

11:22.458 --> 11:26.166
and I unintentionally raised $2,000
for my problem.

11:26.166 --> 11:29.208
Samantha, when you were 4
you couldn't dance either.

11:29.208 --> 11:31.500
Until I pushed you

11:31.500 --> 11:33.667
and I made you practice.

11:33.667 --> 11:36.291
And then when you were 7
you started bringing home trophies.

11:36.291 --> 11:37.667
A Newly never gives up.

11:37.667 --> 11:39.250
It's over, Mom.

11:39.250 --> 11:42.083
The one good thing about my life
and it's just gone.

11:42.917 --> 11:46.917
All right, I'm just gonna go get my stuff
and head back to the city.

11:51.792 --> 11:53.083
Unless you push me again.

11:54.583 --> 11:56.333
No. Oh, no, no, no.

11:56.333 --> 11:57.792
That was hard on both of us.

11:57.792 --> 12:01.417
Oh, no, no. There were so many tears,
so many vodka tonics.

12:01.417 --> 12:04.417
Come on, come on.
You just said that a Newly never gives up.

12:04.417 --> 12:07.083
On themselves.

12:07.083 --> 12:08.625
On each other, all the time.

12:12.333 --> 12:14.083
Come on.

12:15.083 --> 12:16.834
Come on.

12:18.834 --> 12:21.625
And turn. And turn. And turn.

12:21.625 --> 12:23.417
- I don't see hips. Turn.
- That's my hip.

12:23.583 --> 12:25.750
- My hip is out.
- That's one hip. Cha, cha, cha.

12:26.041 --> 12:28.291
- I wasn't ready. I wasn't ready.
- All right. Ready?

12:28.291 --> 12:31.917
- One, two, release. Let go!
- Wait. I just-- Okay, but--

12:31.917 --> 12:34.000
- I don't see a dancer anywhere.
- I am a dancer.

12:34.000 --> 12:36.041
- You are not a dancer.
- I am so a dancer!

12:36.041 --> 12:38.667
- I can't hear you.
- I'm a dancer!

12:38.667 --> 12:40.041
Then show me you're a dancer--

12:40.041 --> 12:41.208
[BELL DINGS]

12:41.208 --> 12:43.041
Sorry, honey.
Gotta turn the chicken over.

12:43.041 --> 12:46.875
And round and round and step
and cha, cha, cha.

12:46.875 --> 12:48.542
- That was it.
- Do it again.

12:48.542 --> 12:51.375
- I wanna go. And step back--
- Step and-- That's my girl!

12:51.375 --> 12:54.208
Yes, yes! You did it!
I knew you could do it!

12:54.208 --> 12:56.000
I think somebody
deserves some ice cream.

12:56.000 --> 12:59.041
I think someone deserves some fresh fruit.
I do have to lift you.

13:02.500 --> 13:05.041
Why should I pay some hack
for taking crap photographs

13:05.041 --> 13:06.625
and ruining my wedding?

13:06.625 --> 13:08.667
We really couldn't do any of this
through e-mail?

13:09.208 --> 13:11.625
Look, Jeffrey looks hideous.

13:11.625 --> 13:13.959
He isn't even smiling,
and it's his wedding day.

13:15.083 --> 13:17.959
There's nothing wrong with these.
Your husband looks hot. Pay the man.

13:17.959 --> 13:21.291
Okay, I don't expect somebody
without a ring on her finger to understand.

13:21.709 --> 13:25.583
You just resent women like me
because you want what we have.

13:25.583 --> 13:29.083
Okay, one,
I've probably already had what you have,

13:29.083 --> 13:32.959
and two, maybe there's no ring
on my finger because I don't want one.

13:32.959 --> 13:35.583
- You don't know me.
- Oh, really?

13:35.583 --> 13:39.667
Career girl by day, and by night
a long line of meaningless affairs

13:39.667 --> 13:42.959
with guys who wouldn't remember you
if they bumped into you on the street.

13:42.959 --> 13:44.750
Am I close?

13:44.750 --> 13:46.875
Just putting off the day
when you find yourself

13:46.875 --> 13:49.208
dancing next to girls
who are ten years younger than you

13:49.208 --> 13:50.834
and you realize
you've missed your window.

13:51.250 --> 13:53.375
And you end up
in your lonely little apartment,

13:53.375 --> 13:57.417
curled up in front of the television,
eating your sad-looking meatloaf for one

13:57.417 --> 14:01.542
and wearing a sweatshirt that says,
"Forget love, I'm falling in chocolate."

14:03.875 --> 14:05.834
Okay, you know what?

14:07.333 --> 14:09.166
I'm gonna take a ten-minute recess.

14:09.166 --> 14:10.667
No, I don't need ten minutes.

14:10.667 --> 14:13.667
I don't care if you pay me or not,
because those pictures are great.

14:13.667 --> 14:15.208
- The problem is you.
- Excuse me?

14:15.208 --> 14:17.542
When I look at these,
I see a guy who loves his wife,

14:17.542 --> 14:18.875
and all you see are the flaws.

14:18.875 --> 14:21.583
You women complain
that there aren't any good guys out there,

14:21.583 --> 14:23.250
then you find one who treats you well

14:23.250 --> 14:25.583
and remembers
that your favorite flower is the daffodil

14:25.583 --> 14:27.500
and held your hand
while you were in a coma--

14:27.500 --> 14:28.917
- What?
- Even after you cheated.

14:28.917 --> 14:30.583
- I never cheated.
- And you still think

14:30.583 --> 14:32.083
there's something better out there.

14:32.083 --> 14:35.000
So you turn to the one guy
who actually loves you and you say,

14:35.000 --> 14:38.417
"You know what, we're not right together.
You have to move out."

14:38.417 --> 14:40.792
Well, you know what?
I am moving out, all right?

14:40.792 --> 14:43.041
I don't care if I have to live in a box.

14:44.208 --> 14:46.542
And for your information,
a guy did offer to marry me.

14:46.542 --> 14:50.166
And if that stick would have turned blue,
I'd be living in Scarsdale by now. Uh-huh.

14:53.709 --> 14:56.208
Hey, Todd, it's me.
Just wanted to let you know

14:56.208 --> 14:58.875
that I am not gonna be coming back
to the apartment tonight

14:58.875 --> 15:02.125
because I have to rehearse my dance
number with my mom in the morning.

15:02.125 --> 15:03.875
It's kind of fun hanging out with her.

15:03.875 --> 15:06.792
I didn't think that I would really like--
Okay, nice beep. All right.

15:06.792 --> 15:10.083
Mom! Hey, I got the dresses!

15:10.083 --> 15:11.917
Mom!

15:11.917 --> 15:13.917
[CHA-CHA MUSIC PLAYING]

15:16.917 --> 15:18.625
Mom?

15:19.083 --> 15:22.166
- What are you doing?
- It's not what it looks like.

15:22.166 --> 15:24.709
You're practicing for the contest with Dad,
aren't you?

15:24.709 --> 15:25.917
No.

15:26.542 --> 15:29.208
We were smoking marijuana.
I am so hungry.

15:29.208 --> 15:30.875
- Who wants pie?
- There's pie.

15:32.041 --> 15:35.291
Here, Dad, I hope you can pull off
something with spaghetti straps.

15:41.875 --> 15:44.166
Samantha.

15:44.166 --> 15:48.709
You were making real progress, honey,
but you only got the one step.

15:48.709 --> 15:52.291
Now, if the competition was one step long,
that trophy would have been ours.

15:52.291 --> 15:54.333
No, no, no, you're right.

15:54.333 --> 15:56.959
I mean, I was just being stupid.

15:56.959 --> 15:59.500
- We would never have won as a team.
- Oh...

15:59.500 --> 16:02.917
Plus, this is really the push I needed.

16:02.917 --> 16:07.083
What am I doing hanging out here all day
dancing with my mommy, right?

16:07.083 --> 16:09.792
I mean, I'm an adult.

16:11.250 --> 16:13.041
Thanks for doing my laundry.

16:13.041 --> 16:14.208
[SNIFFS]

16:14.208 --> 16:16.625
Mm, that really does smell good.

16:22.333 --> 16:23.500
What is that look for?

16:24.500 --> 16:27.291
She said herself she knew
we couldn't beat Paula Drake.

16:27.291 --> 16:29.625
She practically moved back home.

16:29.625 --> 16:31.917
You guys have been out in that garage
ten hours a day.

16:31.917 --> 16:33.875
She did it to be with you.

16:33.875 --> 16:36.000
Howard, please,
I know my own daughter.

16:36.000 --> 16:39.041
She hasn't wanted to spend time with me
since she was 12 years old.

16:39.041 --> 16:41.750
Can we please go back out there?
We've got a lot of work to do.

16:41.750 --> 16:44.417
You know, I think I'm done for tonight.

16:44.417 --> 16:46.458
I don't even want any pie.

16:54.291 --> 16:57.458
That bride messengered over the check
this morning.

16:57.458 --> 17:00.917
There's enough here
for first and last month's rent plus security.

17:00.917 --> 17:03.375
Huh. What I said must have
gotten through.

17:03.375 --> 17:05.291
No, what you said
scared the crap out of her.

17:05.291 --> 17:07.125
I had to talk her out
of a restraining order.

17:07.542 --> 17:09.208
Great.

17:09.208 --> 17:10.667
So...

17:13.250 --> 17:16.250
- Now I can move out.
- Yeah, and Sam can get on with her life.

17:16.250 --> 17:18.166
- And there we are. Thanks, Andrea.
- Mm-hm.

17:18.166 --> 17:20.792
- Andrea.
- Right. Right.

17:20.792 --> 17:23.000
And, hey, listen-- Um...

17:23.500 --> 17:26.917
You're not going to end up alone,
making meatloaf for one.

17:30.083 --> 17:34.375
And somewhere out there,
there's a girl who's just gonna--

17:34.375 --> 17:36.041
Sorry, I can't do it, it's too weird.

17:36.041 --> 17:37.375
We tried.

17:38.166 --> 17:40.166
[JAZZ PLAYING]@n

17:42.041 --> 17:43.709
[CHATTERING]

17:58.417 --> 17:59.542
Who is that guy?

18:01.417 --> 18:02.750
[AUDIENCE APPLAUDING]

18:10.875 --> 18:13.333
That was Drake and Romero.

18:14.375 --> 18:15.667
You guys are next.

18:15.667 --> 18:17.500
I will deny that we had this conversation,

18:17.500 --> 18:19.250
but I'm gonna give you guys
some extra light.

18:23.500 --> 18:25.542
I was just warming them up for you,
Regina.

18:25.542 --> 18:28.291
- Where's Charlie?
- Poor thing hurt his knee.

18:28.291 --> 18:30.375
But fortunately, my good friend Mateo,

18:30.375 --> 18:32.625
three-time international
ballroom-dancing champion,

18:32.625 --> 18:34.917
- was able to be with me.
- So when do I get my money?

18:35.458 --> 18:38.291
ANNOUNCER:
Now, please welcome, next to the floor,

18:38.291 --> 18:43.709
Newly and Newly, and the cha-cha.

18:45.000 --> 18:47.041
[MUSIC PLAYING]

18:47.375 --> 18:49.166
You ready, Regina?

18:49.458 --> 18:50.875
Hurt your knee.

18:50.875 --> 18:52.875
I think the expression is "break a leg."

18:52.875 --> 18:56.583
I swear to God, if you don't hurt your knee
right now, I'll break it with a pipe.

19:00.291 --> 19:01.375
[GROANING]

19:02.542 --> 19:05.834
- Oh, the pain, it's on fire. Oh...
- Easy, De Niro.

19:05.834 --> 19:07.917
Flamingo down. Flamingo down.

19:07.917 --> 19:10.959
- Weber and Duncan on deck.
MAN: I don't believe it.

19:12.250 --> 19:14.250
What's going on? Are you okay?

19:14.250 --> 19:17.041
I'm so happy you came. I was afraid
that was going to be our last fight.

19:17.583 --> 19:20.750
No, Mom.
I want to have lots of fights with you.

19:21.333 --> 19:24.792
I mean, it's only been a year
since we started over, right?

19:24.792 --> 19:26.417
What kid leaves home after a year?

19:27.375 --> 19:31.375
Oh, it's getting worse!
It's like a branding iron searing my flesh!

19:31.375 --> 19:32.875
It hurts, we get it.

19:32.875 --> 19:36.250
ANNOUNCER:
So last chance for Newly and Newly?

19:36.250 --> 19:38.125
Not on your life. Ready?

19:38.125 --> 19:41.083
What, me? Mom, you won't win.

19:41.083 --> 19:42.875
No, Samantha. We won't win.

19:44.583 --> 19:46.375
I was hoping you would ask.

19:46.750 --> 19:49.208
- Here, take this. Take this.
- Okay. All right.

19:49.208 --> 19:50.875
- Positions.
- Positions.

19:50.875 --> 19:52.875
[CHA-CHA MUSIC PLAYING]

20:03.875 --> 20:05.750
Oh, my God, we're doing it.

20:06.375 --> 20:08.041
And--

20:12.083 --> 20:14.542
<i>You know when you think</i>
<i>something is going to go badly</i>

20:14.542 --> 20:17.125
<i>and it goes just okay</i>
<i>so you think it's going great?</i>

20:19.375 --> 20:21.125
<i>It's probably worse</i>
<i>than you ever imagined.</i>

20:30.709 --> 20:34.291
Are you sure you want more light?
Because I was thinking more darkness.

20:46.083 --> 20:48.291
We don't have to go through this
to see each other.

20:48.291 --> 20:49.750
Just come over. I'll be there.

20:50.125 --> 20:52.291
- That's good to know. Thanks.
- Well, call first.

20:52.291 --> 20:53.875
- I do have a life.
- Yeah.

20:53.875 --> 20:55.583
<i>Okay, maybe I was wrong.</i>

20:55.583 --> 20:58.750
<i>Maybe I didn't lose every good thing</i>
<i>with my amnesia.</i>

20:58.750 --> 21:01.375
<i>Some things are in there to discover.</i>

21:01.375 --> 21:03.500
<i>Some can be re-learned.</i>

21:03.500 --> 21:06.041
<i>And others, if they're important,</i>

21:06.041 --> 21:09.750
<i>well, I just gotta trust they'll be there</i>
<i>when I need them.</i>

21:13.542 --> 21:15.500
[MUSIC STOPS]
